Divorce Granted.

In the celebrated Ernst divorce suit from Black Diamond Judge Hanford granted a decree of divorce in favor of the plaintiff, Mary C. Ernst, dissolving the matrimonial bonds which have held her legally to her runaway husband, Jacob Ernst, who deserted her August 20, 1887. Mrs. Ernst gets the custody of their ten-year-old child, Nellie.
